{"article_id":"NWf9liTfa81k8sRG","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Sen. Rand Paul declared victory Thursday","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"after Attorney General Eric Holder assured him","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"that the president can not use a drone","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"to kill a noncombatant American on U.S. soil","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"-- an assurance","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"Paul had sought during his 13-hour filibuster the day before .","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"`` Hooray ! ''","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"Paul responded","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"when the letter was read to him for the first time during an interview with Fox News .","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"`` For 13 hours yesterday , we asked him that question ,","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"so there is a result and a victory .","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"Under duress and under public humiliation , the White House will respond","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"and do the right thing . ''","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"During his dramatic filibuster ,","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"which delayed a vote on CIA director nominee John Brennan ,","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"Paul had demanded the administration clarify the government 's authority","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"to kill on U.S. soil .","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"The filibuster ended past midnight early Thursday morning .","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"The Senate voted , 63-34 , to confirm Brennan later Thursday afternoon .","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"Shortly before the vote , Holder sent a terse letter to Paul","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"that read :","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"`` It has come to my attention that you have now asked an additional question :","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"'Does the President have the authority","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"to use a weaponized drone","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"to kill an American","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"not engaged in combat on American soil ? '","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"The answer to that question is no . ''","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"In response , Paul said Thursday","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"that `` we 're proud to announce","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"that the president is not going to kill unarmed Americans on American soil . ''","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"He later took to the floor","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"to promote the attorney general 's response ,","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"as the Senate moved to confirm Brennan .","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"Though Paul 's 13-hour stand drew praise from all sides of the political spectrum ,","depth":4},{"id":34,"text":"the senator also took heat Thursday from some in his own party","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"who claimed","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"he stirred unnecessary fear about the use of drones .","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"The senator `` should know better , ''","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"Sen. John McCain , R-Ariz. , said ,","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"arguing","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"that some of the concerns","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"raised about drone missile attacks on Americans","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"-- like Paul 's suggestion","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"that the U.S. could have killed Jane Fonda","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"when she went to North Vietnam --","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"were `` ridiculous . ''","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"Sen. Lindsey Graham , R-S.C. , displayed a sign","depth":5},{"id":47,"text":"that showed the number of Americans","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"killed in the U.S. by Al Qaeda","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"-- 2,958 --","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"versus the number","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"killed in the U.S. by drones ,","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"which is zero .","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"Paul , though , argued","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"that he was raising concern about how future presidents might use their drone authority .","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"Paul told Fox News the critical senators","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"`` think","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"the whole world is a battlefield ,","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"including America . ''","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"`` I do n't think","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"the laws of war apply to America .","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"I think","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"the Bill of Rights do , ''","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"Paul said .","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"While the Obama administration increasingly employs armed drones as a pivotal counterterrorism tool overseas ,","depth":4},{"id":65,"text":"domestic law enforcement agencies are also moving to broaden the use of surveillance mini-drones over the next several years .","depth":6},{"id":66,"text":"The Federal Aviation Administration projects as many as 10,000 licensed systems by 2017 .","depth":6},{"id":67,"text":"The lethal drones","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"used in Pakistan","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"are a far cry from the unarmed eyes in the sky","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"used in America .","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"But Paul and a host of other lawmakers see constitutional pitfalls across the board","depth":5},{"id":72,"text":"-- namely focusing on how armed , and unarmed , drones might someday be used against American citizens .","depth":5},{"id":73,"text":"Paul and the senators from both sides of the aisle","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"who joined him on the floor Wednesday","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"described a bleak future","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"in which an unscrupulous government might use drones against its own population","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"if left unchecked .","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"`` Your notification is the buzz of propellers on the drone","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"as it flies overhead in the seconds","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"before you 're killed .","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"Is that what we really want from our government ? ''","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"Paul asked .","depth":6},{"id":83,"text":"Lawmakers have already started pushing legislation","depth":6},{"id":84,"text":"to rein in the drone program","depth":6},{"id":85,"text":"-- legislation","depth":6},{"id":86,"text":"that might get a second look after Paul 's dramatic performance Wednesday .","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"Rep. Zoe Lofgren , D-Calif. , and Ted Poe , R-Texas , last month introduced a bill","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"to regulate domestic drones","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"much like the government regulates wiretaps .","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"It would require officials to obtain a warrant","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"in order to perform many kinds of surveillance with those drones .","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"Further , it would prohibit law enforcement drones from being equipped with firearms or explosives in U.S. airspace .","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"`` As we enter this uncharted world of drone technology ,","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"Congress must be proactive","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"and establish boundaries for drone use","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"that safeguard the constitutional rights of Americans , ''","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"Poe said in a statement last month .","depth":6},{"id":98,"text":"The use of armed drones in U.S. airspace fueled Paul 's lengthy filibuster Wednesday .","depth":5},{"id":99,"text":"Before he took the floor ,","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"Paul announced","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"that he had received a letter from Holder","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"which opened the door , in extremely rare circumstances , to using a drone","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"to kill someone within U.S. territory .","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"Holder said","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"`` catastrophic '' attacks such as the Sept. 11 attacks or the attack on Pearl Harbor are examples of circumstances","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"where the president could conceivably feel","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"such an action is necessary .","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"Testifying on Capitol Hill on Wednesday ,","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"Holder agreed","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"that it would be unconstitutional to use a drone on American soil against a U.S. citizen or a suspected terrorist","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"who did not pose an imminent threat .","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"Paul , during his filibuster , said","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"he wanted a formal assurance from the administration","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"that it would not use drones","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"to kill noncombatant Americans ,","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"which prompted the Holder letter Thursday .","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"Aside from the legislation in the House , members of the Senate Intelligence Committee have floated the idea","depth":5},{"id":118,"text":"of establishing a sort of drone court","depth":7},{"id":119,"text":"to screen potential targets","depth":7},{"id":120,"text":"-- much like a court screens surveillance of foreign targets in the U.S .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":241,"left":184,"right":240,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":184,"left":153,"right":183,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":153,"left":133,"right":152,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":133,"left":129,"right":132,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":129,"left":126,"right":128,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":126,"left":0,"right":125,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":123,"right":124,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":1,"right":122,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":122,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":124,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":6,"right":127,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":132,"left":130,"right":131,"relation":"elaboratio